inating and riveting history of the discourse on racism, antisemitism, and psychopathology, Are Racists Crazy? connects past and present claims about race and racism, showing the dangerous implications of this specious line of thought for today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAntisemitismxPsychological aspects. 0aMental illness. 0aPrejudicesxPsychological aspects. 0aRacismxPsychological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aThomas, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479894758.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479894758423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479894758/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles